      <Placemark>
        <name>Plitvice Lakes National Park</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 106<br>id_no: 98<br>rev_bis: Bis<br>short_description_en: <p>The waters flowing over the limestone and chalk have, over thousands of years, deposited travertine barriers, creating natural dams which in turn have created a series of beautiful lakes, caves and waterfalls. These geological processes continue today. The forests in the park are home to bears, wolves and many rare bird species.</p><br>justification_en: <br>date_inscribed: 1979<br>longitude: 15.61444<br>latitude: 44.87778<br>area_hectares: 29,630.77<br>category: Natural<br>category_short: N<br>states_name_en: Croatia<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: hr<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-seq2-1-8-FFEA00</styleUrl>
