      <Placemark>
        <name>Historic Centre of Avignon: Papal Palace, Episcopal Ensemble and Avignon Bridge</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 254<br>id_no: 228<br>rev_bis: rev<br>short_description_en: <p>In the 14th century, this city in the South of France was the seat of the papacy. The Palais des Papes, an austere-looking fortress lavishly decorated by Simone Martini and Matteo Giovanetti, dominates the city, the surrounding ramparts and the remains of a 12th-century bridge over the Rhone. Beneath this outstanding example of Gothic architecture, the Petit Palais and the Romanesque Cathedral of Notre-Dame-des-Doms complete an exceptional group of monuments that testify to the leading role played by Avignon in 14th-century Christian Europe.</p><br>justification_en: <br>date_inscribed: 1995<br>longitude: 4.806111111<br>latitude: 43.95277778<br>area_hectares: 8.2<br>category: Cultural<br>category_short: C<br>states_name_en: France<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: fr<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-seq2-1-25-FFEA00</styleUrl>
