      <Placemark>
        <name>Würzburg Residence with the Court Gardens and Residence Square</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 1735<br>id_no: 169<br>rev_bis: Bis<br>short_description_en: <p>This magnificent Baroque palace – one of the largest and most beautiful in Germany and surrounded by wonderful gardens – was created under the patronage of the prince-bishops Lothar Franz and Friedrich Carl von Schönborn. It was built and decorated in the 18th century by an international team of architects, painters (including Tiepolo), sculptors and stucco-workers, led by Balthasar Neumann.</p><br>justification_en: <br>date_inscribed: 1981<br>longitude: 9.93889<br>latitude: 49.79278<br>area_hectares: 14.77<br>category: Cultural<br>category_short: C<br>states_name_en: Germany<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: de<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
