      <Placemark>
        <name>Pilgrimage Church of Wies</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 1864<br>id_no: 271<br>rev_bis: Bis<br>short_description_en: <p>Miraculously preserved in the beautiful setting of an Alpine valley, the Church of Wies (1745&ndash;54), the work of architect Dominikus Zimmermann, is a masterpiece of Bavarian Rococo &ndash; exuberant, colourful and joyful.</p><br>justification_en: <br>date_inscribed: 1983<br>longitude: 10.90013889<br>latitude: 47.68127778<br>area_hectares: 0.1<br>category: Cultural<br>category_short: C<br>states_name_en: Germany<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: de<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
