      <Placemark>
        <name>Rock Drawings in Valcamonica</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 101<br>id_no: 94<br>rev_bis: <br>short_description_en: <p>Valcamonica, situated in the Lombardy plain, has one of the world's greatest collections of prehistoric petroglyphs – more than 140,000 symbols and figures carved in the rock over a period of 8,000 years and depicting themes connected with agriculture, navigation, war and magic.</p><br>justification_en: <br>date_inscribed: 1979<br>longitude: 10.29733333<br>latitude: 45.95705556<br>area_hectares: 432.3<br>category: Cultural<br>category_short: C<br>states_name_en: Italy<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: it<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
