      <Placemark>
        <name>Piazza del Duomo, Pisa</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 1558<br>id_no: 395<br>rev_bis: Bis<br>short_description_en: Standing in a large green expanse, Piazza del Duomo houses a group of monuments known the world over. These four masterpieces of medieval architecture – the cathedral, the baptistry, the campanile (the 'Leaning Tower') and the cemetery – had a great influence on monumental art in Italy from the 11th to the 14th century.<br>justification_en: <br>date_inscribed: 1987<br>longitude: 10.39638889<br>latitude: 43.72305556<br>area_hectares: 8.87<br>category: Cultural<br>category_short: C<br>states_name_en: Italy<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: it<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
