      <Placemark>
        <name>Portovenere, Cinque Terre, and the Islands (Palmaria, Tino and Tinetto)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 2458<br>id_no: 826<br>rev_bis: <br>short_description_en: <p>The Ligurian coast between Cinque Terre and Portovenere is a cultural landscape of great scenic and cultural value. The layout and disposition of the small towns and the shaping of the surrounding landscape, overcoming the disadvantages of a steep, uneven terrain, encapsulate the continuous history of human settlement in this region over the past millennium.</p><br>justification_en: <p>The Committee decided to inscribe this site on the basis of criteria (ii), (iv) and (v), considering that the eastern Ligurian Riviera between Cinque Terre and Portovenere is a cultural site of outstanding value, representing the harmonious interaction between people and nature to produce a landscape of exceptional scenic quality that illustrates a traditional way of life that has existed for a thousand years and continues to play an important socio-economic role in the life of the community.</p><br>date_inscribed: 1997<br>longitude: 9.72917<br>latitude: 44.10694<br>area_hectares: 4,689.25<br>category: Cultural<br>category_short: C<br>states_name_en: Italy<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: it<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
