      <Placemark>
        <name>Old City of Berne</name>
        <description><![CDATA[unique_number: 297<br>id_no: 267<br>rev_bis: <br>short_description_en: <p>Founded in the 12th century on a hill site surrounded by the Aare River, Berne developed over the centuries in line with a an exceptionally coherent planning concept. The buildings in the Old City, dating from a variety of periods, include 15th-century arcades and 16th-century fountains. Most of the medieval town was restored in the 18th century but it has retained its original character.</p><br>justification_en: <br>date_inscribed: 1983<br>longitude: 7.45028<br>latitude: 46.94806<br>area_hectares: 84.684<br>category: Cultural<br>category_short: C<br>states_name_en: Switzerland<br>region_en: Europe and North America<br>iso_code: ch<br>transboundary: 0]]></description>
