          </Data>
          <Data name="short_description_en">
            <value><![CDATA[<p>The Bellinzona site consists of a group of fortifications grouped around the castle of Castelgrande, which stands on a rocky peak looking out over the entire Ticino valley. Running from the castle, a series of fortified walls protect the ancient town and block the passage through the valley. A second castle (Montebello) forms an integral part of the fortifications, while a third but separate castle (Sasso Corbaro) was built on an isolated rocky promontory south-east of the other fortifications.</p>]]></value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="justification_en">
            <value><![CDATA[<p><em>Criterion (iv):</em> The fortified ensemble of Bellinzona is an outstanding example of a late medieval defensive structure guarding a key strategic Alpine pass.</p>]]></value>
